The paper deals with the problem of recovering a structured signal from dimensionality-reduced linear measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and imaging. The approach taken in the paper is a learning-based one, where a fixed index set is chosen based on a set of training signals. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Among these, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with optimization problems and theoretical guarantees, which are common topics in these sub-fields.
